  "prompt": "Can you be a pilot if you wear glasses?",
  "response": "Yes, you can be a pilot even if you wear glasses. The Federal Aviation Administration (FAA) and other aviation authorities around the world allow individuals with vision correction to become pilots. However, there are specific vision requirements that must be met.\n\nFor example, in the United States, the FAA requires that a pilot's distant vision must be correctable to 20/20 or better in each eye, and near vision must be 20/40 or better. Additionally, if you wear glasses, you must have a spare pair with you while flying.\n\nIt's important to consult with an Aviation Medical Examiner (AME) to ensure that your vision meets the necessary standards and to discuss any other medical requirements for obtaining and maintaining a pilot's license.",
